Changelog

Sourced from react-router's changelog.

7.8.1

Patch Changes

  • Fix usage of optional path segments in nested routes defined using absolute paths (#14135)
  • Bubble client pre-next middleware error to the shallowest ancestor that needs to load, not strictly the shallowest ancestor with a loader (#14150)
  • Fix optional static segment matching in matchPath (#11813)
  • Fix prerendering when a basename is set with ssr:false (#13791)
  • Provide isRouteErrorResponse utility in react-server environments (#14166)
  • Propagate non-redirect Responses thrown from middleware to the error boundary on document/data requests (#14182)
  • Handle meta and links Route Exports in RSC Data Mode (#14136)
  • Properly convert returned/thrown data() values to Response instances via Response.json() in resource routes and middleware (#14159, #14181)

7.8.0

Minor Changes

  • Add nonce prop to Links & PrefetchPageLinks (#14048)
  • Add loaderData arguments/properties alongside existing data arguments/properties to provide consistency and clarity between loaderData and actionData across the board (#14047)
    • Updated types: Route.MetaArgs, Route.MetaMatch, MetaArgs, MetaMatch, Route.ComponentProps.matches, UIMatch
    • @deprecated warnings have been added to the existing data properties to point users to new loaderData properties, in preparation for removing the data properties in a future major release

Patch Changes

  • Prevent "Did not find corresponding fetcher result" console error when navigating during a fetcher.submit revalidation (#14114)

  • Bubble client-side middleware errors prior to next to the appropriate ancestor error boundary (#14138)

  • Switch Lazy Route Discovery manifest URL generation to usea standalone URLSearchParams instance instead of URL.searchParams to avoid a major performance bottleneck in Chrome (#14084)

  • Adjust internal RSC usage of React.use to avoid Webpack compilation errors when using React 18 (#14113)

  • Remove dependency on @types/node in TypeScript declaration files (#14059)

  • Fix types for UIMatch to reflect that the loaderData/data properties may be undefined (#12206)

    • When an ErrorBoundary is being rendered, not all active matches will have loader data available, since it may have been their loader that threw to trigger the boundary
    • The UIMatch.data type was not correctly handing this and would always reflect the presence of data, leading to the unexpected runtime errors when an ErrorBoundary was rendered
    • ‚ö†Ô∏è This may cause some type errors to show up in your code for unguarded match.data accesses - you should properly guard for undefined values in those scenarios.
    // app/root.tsx
export function loader() {
  someFunctionThatThrows(); // ‚ùå Throws an Error
  return { title: "My Title" };
}

let matches = useMatches();
let rootMatch = matches[0] as UIMatch<Awaited<ReturnType<typeof loader>>>;
//  ^ rootMatch.data is incorrectly typed here, so TypeScript does not

pull_request.title: Debug persian voice chatbot connection issues on vercel
pull_request.body: Fixes voice service connection issues by enabling dynamic backend URL configuration and enhancing WebSocket stability and Persian voice processing. The "ŸÇÿ∑ÿπ ÿßÿ±ÿ™ÿ®ÿßÿ∑" error stemmed from a hardcoded, non-existent backend WebSocket URL and a lack of robust connection management. This PR addresses these by introducing environment-based URL configuration, implementing exponential backoff for WebSocket reconnections, and integrating real Persian Speech-to-Text and Text-to-Speech engines, replacing previous mock implementations. ---

commits.message:
Configures bcrypt salt rounds from environment

This change allows configuring the number of salt rounds used by bcrypt
from an environment variable.  This provides flexibility to adjust
the security/performance tradeoff without modifying code.

Implements user registration with transaction

Enhances user registration process by adding database
transaction to ensure atomicity.
Adds a default permission to newly registered users.

Rolls back transaction on failure to maintain data consistency.

Adds permission check to login endpoint

Implements permission verification during login to restrict user access.
Users are now only granted a token if they have the necessary permission.
Updates the registration process to only create a permissions entry with the user ID.
Modifies frontend redirect after login to use absolute path.

Enhances authentication and navigation flow

Improves the authentication process by using JWT for secure tokens and environment variables for secrets.
The frontend is updated to ensure the navigation is loaded before certain pages, preventing issues with initial page load.
Additionally, the permission check in the backend is made more robust.

Serves frontend routes from a single entry point

Ensures all frontend routes are served from the index.html file.

This change centralizes frontend routing, simplifying the application's structure and ensuring consistent handling of navigation.

issue.title: [Bug] Installing opentelemetry bundle breaks existing Monolog config
issue.body:
**Problem**

After installing `friendsofopentelemetry/opentelemetry-bundle`, I've created the [config](https://friendsofopentelemetry.github.io/opentelemetry-bundle/user-guide/getting-started.html#usage) like stated in the docs, and then wanted to dump the reference config with `config:dump-reference open_telemetry` (like stated in the [configuration](https://friendsofopentelemetry.github.io/opentelemetry-bundle/user-guide/configuration.html) section). 

I have an existing `monolog.yaml` like this.

```yaml
monolog:
  channels:
    - deprecation # Deprecations are logged in the dedicated "deprecation" channel when it exists
  handlers:
    deprecation:
      type: "null"
      channels: [ deprecation ]

when@dev:
  monolog:
    handlers:
      main:
        type: stream
        path: "%kernel.logs_dir%/%kernel.environment%.log"
        level: debug
        channels: [ "!event" ]
      # uncomment to get logging in your browser
      # you may have to allow bigger header sizes in your Web server configuration
      #firephp:
      #    type: firephp
      #    level: info
      #chromephp:
      #    type: chromephp
      #    level: info
      console:
        type: console
        process_psr_3_messages: false
        channels: [ "!event", "!doctrine", "!console" ]

when@test:
  monolog:
    handlers:
      main:
        type: fingers_crossed
        action_level: error
        handler: nested
        excluded_http_codes: [ 404, 405 ]
        channels: [ "!event" ]
      nested:
        type: stream
        path: "%kernel.logs_dir%/%kernel.environment%.log"
        level: debug

when@prod:
  monolog:
    handlers:
      main:
        type: fingers_crossed
        action_level: error
        handler: nested
        excluded_http_codes: [ 404, 405 ]
        buffer_size: 50 # How many messages should be saved? Prevent memory leaks
      nested:
        type: stream
        path: php://stderr
        level: debug
        formatter: monolog.formatter.json
      console:
        type: console
        process_psr_3_messages: false
        channels: [ "!event", "!doctrine" ]
      deprecation:
        type: stream
        channels: [ deprecation ]
        path: php://stderr
```

When on `APP_ENV=dev`, I've executed `config:dump-reference open_telemetry -vvv` and it gives an error now.

```shell
Monolog configuration error: The logging channel "deprecation" assigned to the "deprecation" handler does not exist
```

task: [app:console] docker compose exec $TTY phpfpm bin/console config:dump-reference open_telemetry -vvv

In LoggerChannelPass.php line 104:
